content: Place in Singapore **Pulau Anak Bukom** is a small 0.2-[hectare](/wiki/Hectare) [islet](/wiki/Islet) located to the south west of Singapore, between [Pulau Bukom](/wiki/Pulau_Bukom) and Pulau Bukom Kechil. *Anak Bukom* means "child of Bukom" in [Malay](/wiki/Malay_language), a reference to its small size and location just next to Pulau Bukom. - Satellite image of Pulau Anak Bukum - [Google Maps](/wiki/Google_Maps) This [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore) location article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it. - v - t - e
